<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,224,2004]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Male imago. Length (mm): body, 9.0–12.0; fore wing, 
<number box="[871,976,560,586]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="10.35" valueMax="11.2" valueMin="9.5">9.5–11.2</number>
; hind wing, 
<number box="[1132,1223,560,586]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="4.699999999999999" valueMax="5.3" valueMin="4.1">4.1–5.3</number>
; foreleg, 
<number box="[1340,1431,560,586]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="5.0" valueMax="5.8" valueMin="4.2">4.2–5.8</number>
; cerci, 26.0–33.0. General coloration yellowish white shaded heavily with brownish gray (much lighter specimens were also collected, but the description below is based on those with the better marked color pattern). Head yellowish white shaded widely with gray on dorsum, except around median ocellus, shaded stronger between lateral ocelli (similar to 
<figureCitation box="[650,739,709,735]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[705,739,709,735]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
). Antennae: scape and pedicel yellowish white completely shaded with gray, flagellum hyaline. Thorax. Pronotum with anterior ring relatively long, strongly shaded with gray dorsally; posterior ring shaded gray except on sublateral areas. Mesonotum whitish yellow shaded widely with gray along medioparapsidal sutures and medial line, and shaded with black on a V-shaped mark between posterior scutal protuberances. Metanotum whitish yellow shaded gray except laterally. Thoracic pleura and sterna whitish yellow, darker on carinae; metasternum shaded with gray in the middle. Legs yellowish white shaded with grayish on fore femur, tibia and first tarsal segment, rest of leg shaded much lighter; middle and hind legs yellowish shaded gray except tarsi whitish. Wings. Membrane hyaline, longitudinal and cross veins translucent shaded slightly with brownish. Abdomen. Tergum I shaded widely with brownish gray except medial band, terga II–VIII shaded more extensively but with a pair of submedian pale marks increasing in size towards rear segments, also with a pale oblique dash laterally; terga IX–X shaded more strongly, IX with pale marks submedially near fore margin and laterally, the lateral pale marks are surrounded with black. Abdominal sterna shaded widely with brownish gray except on pair of submedian spots and along medial and sublateral thin bands. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[856,987,1194,1220]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[910,939,1194,1220]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="63.0">63</number>
–66
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[998,1032,1194,1220]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 80" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 80. SEM photographs. Tortopsis limoncocha: 73, male genitalia, v. v.; 74, apex of penes, detail; 75, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 76, egg. Tortopsis spatula: 77, male genitalia, v. v. and detail of apex of penes; 78, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 79, egg; 80, egg, thread partially uncoiled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195443/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">77</figureCitation>
): sternum IX shaded very strongly in posterior margin; large parastyli orangeish, curved dorsally and with a longitudinal ventral furrow along its entire length (
<figureCitation box="[315,447,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[371,401,1269,1295]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="63.0">63</number>
–65
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[459,492,1269,1295]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 80" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 80. SEM photographs. Tortopsis limoncocha: 73, male genitalia, v. v.; 74, apex of penes, detail; 75, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 76, egg. Tortopsis spatula: 77, male genitalia, v. v. and detail of apex of penes; 78, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 79, egg; 80, egg, thread partially uncoiled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195443/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">77</figureCitation>
); forceps and penes translucent yellowish white, shaded slightly gray on second forceps segment; spine at apex of penes blunt, semicircular (
<figureCitation box="[858,945,1306,1332]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[957,990,1306,1332]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 80" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 80. SEM photographs. Tortopsis limoncocha: 73, male genitalia, v. v.; 74, apex of penes, detail; 75, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 76, egg. Tortopsis spatula: 77, male genitalia, v. v. and detail of apex of penes; 78, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 79, egg; 80, egg, thread partially uncoiled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195443/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">77</figureCitation>
). Caudal filament whitish translucent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,224,2004]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Female imago. Length (mm): body, 11.0–14.0; fore wing, 
<number box="[893,1013,1344,1370]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="13.8" valueMax="15.2" valueMin="12.4">12.4–15.2</number>
; hind wing, 
<number box="[1163,1254,1344,1370]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="5.85" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="5.2">5.2–6.5</number>
; cerci, 
<number box="[1341,1432,1344,1370]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="5.0" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="4.5">4.5–5.5</number>
. General coloration as in male but more strongly marked, eggs yellowish white. Head black between ocelli, with gray anastomosed marks on occiput (
<figureCitation box="[681,777,1418,1444]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[741,777,1418,1444]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with wide sublateral gray band, not well distinguished from the remaining gray marks (
<figureCitation box="[697,785,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[752,785,1456,1482]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
). Wings membrane hyaline slightly tinged with yellow, veins more strongly shaded with brownish. Abdomen shaded uniformly with gray on terga, except on sublateral pale dashes. Sternum VIII with V-shaped parastyli receptors on sternum VIII (
<figureCitation box="[1228,1375,1530,1556]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Figs. 
<number box="[1297,1326,1530,1556]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="61.0">61</number>
–62
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1388,1421,1530,1556]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 80" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 80. SEM photographs. Tortopsis limoncocha: 73, male genitalia, v. v.; 74, apex of penes, detail; 75, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 76, egg. Tortopsis spatula: 77, male genitalia, v. v. and detail of apex of penes; 78, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 79, egg; 80, egg, thread partially uncoiled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195443/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">78</figureCitation>
), margin of socket weakly sclerotized, depression elongated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,224,2004]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Egg (
<figureCitation box="[261,405,1605,1631]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 80" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 80. SEM photographs. Tortopsis limoncocha: 73, male genitalia, v. v.; 74, apex of penes, detail; 75, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 76, egg. Tortopsis spatula: 77, male genitalia, v. v. and detail of apex of penes; 78, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 79, egg; 80, egg, thread partially uncoiled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195443/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Figs. 
<number box="[326,405,1605,1631]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="79.5" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="79.0">79–80</number>
</figureCitation>
). Suboval, with a long thread coiled around the convex area of the egg. Length, 
<number box="[1333,1436,1605,1631]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="352.5" valueMax="375.0" valueMin="330.0">330–375</number>
µm; width, 
<number box="[287,389,1642,1668]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="285.0" valueMax="300.0" valueMin="270.0">270–300</number>
µm. The entire surface is covered by well marked subcircular grooves.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,224,2004]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Observations. The specimens from Amacayacu are very pale, the color pattern is the same but much less marked dorsally, and almost completely absent ventrally.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,224,2004]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Etymology. From the latin &quot; 
<taxonomicName box="[539,631,1754,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatula">spatula</taxonomicName>
&quot;, meaning spoon, an allusion to the flat and thin shape of penean apical spine.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="32.[151,1437,224,2004]" lastBlockId="33.[151,1436,152,290]" lastPageId="33" lastPageNumber="34" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Discussion and diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName box="[536,746,1829,1854]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spatula" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[536,746,1829,1854]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Tortopsis spatula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[762,864,1829,1855]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, known from imagos of both sexes, can be distinguished from all other species of the genus by: 
<number box="[775,788,1866,1892]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="1.0">1</number>
) fore wing length 
<quantity box="[1010,1165,1866,1892]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.035" metricValueMax="1.1199999999999999" metricValueMin="0.95" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="10.35" valueMax="11.2" valueMin="9.5">9.5–11.2 mm</quantity>
(male), 
<quantity box="[1265,1436,1866,1892]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.38" metricValueMax="1.52" metricValueMin="1.24" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="13.8" valueMax="15.2" valueMin="12.4">12.4–15.2 mm</quantity>
(female); 
<number box="[266,282,1904,1930]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="2.0">2</number>
) pale wings, veins translucent hyaline; 
<number box="[748,763,1904,1930]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="3.0">3</number>
) parastyli moderately curved, with a longitudinal ventral furrow (
<figureCitation box="[250,386,1941,1967]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Fig. 
<number box="[308,339,1941,1967]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="63.0">63</number>
–65
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[399,433,1941,1967]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 80" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 80. SEM photographs. Tortopsis limoncocha: 73, male genitalia, v. v.; 74, apex of penes, detail; 75, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 76, egg. Tortopsis spatula: 77, male genitalia, v. v. and detail of apex of penes; 78, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 79, egg; 80, egg, thread partially uncoiled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195443/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">77</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[456,472,1941,1967]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="4.0">4</number>
) apical spine of penes rounded and flattened (
<figureCitation box="[1035,1138,1941,1967]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Figs. 66</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1151,1185,1941,1967]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 80" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 80. SEM photographs. Tortopsis limoncocha: 73, male genitalia, v. v.; 74, apex of penes, detail; 75, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 76, egg. Tortopsis spatula: 77, male genitalia, v. v. and detail of apex of penes; 78, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 79, egg; 80, egg, thread partially uncoiled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195443/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">77</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[1208,1223,1941,1967]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="5.0">5</number>
) female parastyli receptors with V-shaped sockets (
<figureCitation box="[545,688,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
Figs. 
<number box="[612,640,1978,2004]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="61.0">61</number>
–62
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[700,733,1978,2004]" captionStart="FIGURES 73 – 80" captionStartId="27.[151,269,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[188,1398,197,1850]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 73 – 80. SEM photographs. Tortopsis limoncocha: 73, male genitalia, v. v.; 74, apex of penes, detail; 75, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 76, egg. Tortopsis spatula: 77, male genitalia, v. v. and detail of apex of penes; 78, female abdominal sternum VIII, detail of left socket; 79, egg; 80, egg, thread partially uncoiled." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195443/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">78</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[755,770,1978,2004]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" value="6.0">6</number>
) head shaded black behind median ocellus, occiput with gray anastomosed marks (
<figureCitation box="[476,570,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[535,570,152,178]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
); 
<number box="[594,610,152,178]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" value="7.0">7</number>
) female pronotum as described in 
<taxonomicName box="[1044,1341,152,177]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuripennis">
<emphasis box="[1044,1341,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">Tortopsis obscuripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the sublateral gray mark is broad and not completely isolated from the main central shading (
<figureCitation box="[1188,1275,189,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 60 – 66" captionStartId="23.[151,270,1615,1639]" captionTargetBox="[267,1354,408,1573]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[229,1358,383,1589]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 60 – 66. Tortopsis spatula: 60, female head; 61, female abdominal sternum VIII, v. v.; 62, same, l. v.; 63, male genitalia after potash (left forceps and penes omitted); 64, male genitalia, v. v; 65, same, l. v.; 66, details of penes." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195441/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[1242,1275,189,215]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" value="60.0">60</number>
</figureCitation>
). The form of the penean spine suggests a close relationship with 
<taxonomicName box="[748,927,226,251]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Tortopsis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unguiculatus">
<emphasis box="[748,927,226,251]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">T. unguiculatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as recovered in shortest phylogenetic trees with the reduced data set (
<figureCitation box="[458,525,264,290]" captionStart="FIGURE 1. A" captionStartId="4.[151,256,1731,1755]" captionTargetBox="[207,1379,197,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[207,1380,197,1701]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A, strict consensus of 234 shortest trees obtained with the complete data set (58 steps, Ci = 81, Ri = 93); B, strict consensus of 3 shortest trees obtained with the reduced data set (58 steps, Ci = 81, Ri = 92). Values near nodes indicate group support (frequency difference / absolute Bremer Support / relative BS). Black circles indicate unique apomorphies, white circles indicate parallelism or reversal, the small numbers above and below these marks are character and state numbers respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195432/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="34">
Fig. 
<number box="[513,525,264,290]" pageId="33" pageNumber="34" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
